21/11/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Aleksandros Malas, the foreign ministry's director for Balkan issues, met with Macedonian Ambassador to Greece Blagoj Handziski on Friday (19 November). 
They agreed that resolving the name issue between their two countries is a precondition for normalising relations. 
Handziski voiced his country's commitment to continuing talks on the issue under the auspices of the UN. 
Greece has threatened to block Macedonia's entry into the EU and NATO because of the dispute. 
(MIA, Kathimerini - 20/11/04)
